Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Taiwan is now super-aged.\NMore than 4.6 million people here are 65 or older.\NThat is one in five.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:10.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Among them, sarcopenia - the gradual loss of muscle and strength -\Nmay affect roughly one in ten older adults, or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:16.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Falls are the number two cause of accidental injury death in this age group:\Nabout 25 deaths per 100,000 each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:21.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Sarcopenia is linked to about 1.5 to 2 times higher fall risk.\NThat makes movement quality matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:26.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,What helps is well established:\Nregular strength and balance training,\Nfrom sit-to-stand to balance holds and supported squats.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:30.00,Caption,,0,0,0,,Taiwan has nearly 5,000 community care centers.\NBut one worker cannot watch every movement.\NThat is the gap GemmaFit is built to fill.
